but I wanted to say what a great help Graffe's has<br>
been. Anyway my wizard is now 48th level and I wanted<br>
to share something I learned with the rest of you.<br>
<br>
Recently I've gone to TD to Quad Spirocs. Which is<br>
great xp, but occationally I'd get 1 or 2 adds on the<br>
pull. Well after a few times I noticed that it took<br>
a little over 1/2 my mana to do the first 4 and if I then<br>
nuked the other one or 2 down it took the rest.<br>
But if I continued to use CoF it took about the same<br>
amount of mana to take down the other 1 or 2.<br>
<br>
So I got to thinking, maybe I can 8 kite. So I pulled 8<br>
the next time on purpose. I ran around in circles and<br>
cast BoF on them. 4 were snared and the other 4<br>
separated from the main group and came after me.<br>
I ran a little ahead of them and snared them too.<br>
Now I had 2 groups of 4 a little distance apart.<br>
So I started AEing the 1st group. When BoF broke,<br>
I re-cast it, then waited for the other 4 to loose<br>
BoF and re-cast it on them too. Now to save yourself<br>
a lot of mana, what you want to do is the minute<br>
one of the ones you are AEing dies, get both groups<br>
together again and the AE again. This way your AE<br>
isn't wasted on only 3 mobs. your damage leaks over<br>
to the other group and eventually only the other group<br>
remains. If BoF breaks after some are dead, wait until<br>
it breaks for all the remaining mobs before re-snaring<br>
this way you get a group of 4 and a group with the<br>
remainder. But get them back together so that you<br>
can continue to take advantage of the damage leakage.<br>
<br>
I found that I can usually do this without needing to<br>
cast Harvest, but its nice to have it just incase.<br>
<br>
Technically if you had enough mana, you could also 12 kite in the same way.<br>
<br>
Well I hope this helps some of you out Good Luck and<br>
good 8 kiting +.<br>
<br>
Ordin Nookerbottwothousand<br>
48th Wizard<br>
